# 8. お菓子があろうとなかろうと

Tsukasa: Hah hah hah hah! Our Halloween show was a great success!
Emu: Everyone was on the edge of their seats!
Nene: The Halloween theme and clever use of props turned out to be a real draw too.
Rui: Indeed. Seeing everyone smile the way they did during the finale was particularly rewarding.
Mascot: Miss Emu!
Tsukasa: Whoa! This dude keeps jumping out of nowhere...
Rui: Oh, he's usually hiding in that bush over there.
Tsukasa: R-Really? I had no idea.
Mascot: (I didn't think anyone would figure that out...)
Mascot: Ahem! More importantly, Miss Emu, the tallies for the first round of shows were announced today!
Emu: Oh, yeah...
Nene: They already announced them?
Tsukasa: So, how are we doing?!
Mascot: Ah, please take a look here.
Emu: Let's see... We're... Third!!
Nene: Third is... Pretty good, isn't it?
Rui: It is. Especially considering that the groups in first and second are on bigger stages. We're doing rather well.
Nene: We aren't that far behind the group in second either.
Tsukasa: But there's a huge gap in score between us and the Phoenix Stage group in first place.
Tsukasa: Then we need to step up our game!
Tsukasa: We're going to win and star in that commercial!
Tsukasa: I'm counting on you to come up with another amazing show, Mr. Director!
Rui: Oh, of course. I'll chart us a course to reach new heights and see more smiles.
Rui: I also brought some props I'd like to try out for our next show. Would you mind helping me with them?
Emu: Ah, so the pile of stuff behind the stage is yours.
Emu: I've never seen most of these props before! There was this outfit like a space suit and a gizmo that looked like a rocket...
Tsukasa: You're not planning on sending me into space, are you?!
Rui: Follow me this way, Tsukasa...
Tsukasa: Hey, not so fast! I've got a bad feeling about this!
Rui: My idea with the water tank didn't pan out, so I thought that I'd try something in the sky instead...
Tsukasa: What kind of logic is that?! And do you live in some warehouse filled with these insane things?!
Rui: Why not come over and see for yourself...?
Tsukasa: No! No way you're going to lure me there!
Emu: I want to see Rui's house! Let's all visit together!
Tsukasa: I'm NOT going!
Nene: Sigh... Keep it down, will you guys...
Nene: But it's good to see that things are back to normal...
Nene: You know, Rui...
Rui: Yes? What is it, Nene?
Nene: I'm happy.
Nene: I'm happy that we're making shows together again, just like when we were little.
Rui: Hehe, you are?
Nene: There was a time when you were all alone and I had no way to help.
Nene: But it's different now. You can lean on me more. We've been friends since forever, so you can count on me.
Rui: Yeah... Thanks, Nene.
Tsukasa: Hey, let's go home already!
Emu: Why don't we have a party to celebrate our show's success like last time♪
Nene: We can if you want to, but just try to keep the noise down.
Rui: Hehe, I suppose I could come along too. Oh, actually...
Rui: I should go over to SEKAI and give KAITO my thanks.
Rui: But that wouldn't make for much of a visit. It might be better to invite him to see our show.
Rui: Seeing the fruits of our labor, a performance that makes everyone feel good, would be a better gift of gratitude than a few lousy words.
Rui: Also, what should we do for our next show?
Doggie Plushie: I want our next show to be stylish!
Kitty Plushie: Oh, that sounds fun!
Len: Well, look at that. They've made up and are getting along just fine again!
Miku: Phew! That's one less worry♪
Len: How did you make that happen, KAITO?
KAITO: We talked a little. That's all.
KAITO: I wonder what kind of show Rui and his friends are making right now...?
KAITO: Hehe. Something tells me they'll surprise us soon with another amazing performance...
